<div id="stitle" style="display:none;">Notebook Entry</div>
<dl id="n12047d"> <dt class="nbunit"><a name="n12" href="#n12047d">N12 (VI.B.14)</a>:  <a href="../../FF/fnbs/n12all.htm#n12047d"> 47(d)</a></dt> <dd> <blockquote> ~ 1 leader 1 mass, 1 mod / 1 tonsure (ear to ear) / most holy sun</blockquote> <dd class="well"> <blockquote class="sources">St. Aengus divides the Irish Saints into three classes. The first class, extending from the year 432 to 534, begins with St. Patrick, and numbers 350 Saints, all bishops and founders of Churches. The Saints in this class are called &ldquo;<mark>most holy</mark>,&rdquo; and are compared to the <mark>sun</mark> in its meridian splendour. &ldquo;They had one head, our Divine Redeemer; <mark>one leader, St. Patrick; one Mass; one mode of celebration; one tonsure from ear to ear</mark>.&rdquo; <small> Very Rev. Dean Kinane, <a name="TKSP" href="../../FF/fdra/fdex.htm#TKSP"><cite title="source">St. Patrick: his life, his heroic virtues, his labours, and the fruits of his labours</cite></a>, (ed. unknown) 226</small></blockquote> <mm class="note">Raphael transcription: <a name="c12034d" href="c12all.htm#c12034d">VI.C.12:034(d)</a> </mm></dd> </dd></dl>
